    "created_at": "2015-11-26T14:50:08Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-11-26T14:50:08Z",
    "body": "@ahgan84 aren't you getting `did-fail-load` first and only then `dom-ready`? If so, then on `did-fail-load`, you can remove the `dom-ready` listener so the window won't show. Show the error message, close the window and exit.\n\nIf that's not the case (for some reason you get the ready event before the fail event), then you can throw `did-get-response-details` into the mix and show the window only if you get `httpResponseCode` 200 for your url (if you need to support redirects, you'll need to update your url to the `newURL`).\n"
  },
